    <h2>SO WHICH SHOULD YOU CHOOSE?</h2>

    <p>There is no single "best" roofing material, only the best material for your specific situation. Here is a simplified decision framework:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Choose asphalt shingles</strong> if budget is your top priority, you want a quick installation, or you are roofing a rental/investment property.</li>
      <li><strong>Choose metal</strong> if you want the best long-term value, maximum energy savings, and superior storm protection - and are willing to invest more upfront. <a href="/finance">Financing options</a> can make the upgrade more manageable.</li>
      <li><strong>Choose tile</strong> if aesthetics are paramount, your home structure supports the weight, or you live in a community with tile roof requirements.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>The best way to decide is to get a professional assessment of your roof's condition, structure, and your specific needs. Happy Roof installs all three materials as part of our <a href="/residential-roofing">residential roofing services</a> and can help you weigh the pros and cons for your home. We install GAF and Owens Corning shingle products, and Gulf Coast Supply metal panels, so we have hands-on experience with every major option available.</p>

